\f3\fs32 ) and  the combined ALAN and crayfish treatments (0.13) compared to the control (0.05), indicating greater dietary diversity. Aquatic prey consumption was highest in the presence of crayfish, and the trophic niche width was widest when ALAN and crayfish occurred together. \
